## Stacked Nightingale

When multiple Nightingale series are provided, their sectors will be stacked for each category by default:

```js
series: [
    {
        type: 'nightingale',
        angleKey: 'product',
        radiusKey: 'A sales',
    },
    {
        type: 'nightingale',
        angleKey: 'product',
        radiusKey: 'B sales',
    },
],
```

{% chartExampleRunner title="Stacked Nightingale Chart" name="stack-nightingale" type="generated" options="{ \"enterprise\": true }" /%}

## Grouped Nightingale

In a grouped Nightingale series, sectors are placed next to each other. This behaviour is controlled by the `grouped: true` property.  The following example illustrates a grouped Nightingale chart:

```js
series: [
    {
        type: 'nightingale',
        angleKey: 'product',
        radiusKey: 'A sales',
        grouped: true,
    },
    {
        type: 'nightingale',
        angleKey: 'product',
        radiusKey: 'B sales',
        grouped: true,
    },
],
```

{% chartExampleRunner title="Grouped Nightingale Chart" name="group-nightingale" type="generated" options="{ \"enterprise\": true }" /%}

## Axis Styling

There is a way to set a padding between elements. To do this, a few options should be added to the polar **angle** axis. `paddingInner` controls the padding between column groups, and `groupPaddingInner` controls the padding between columns within a group.

```js
axes: [
    {
        type: 'angle-category',
        groupPaddingInner: 0.25,
        paddingInner: 0.25,
    },
    {
        type: 'radius-number',
    },
]
```

{% chartExampleRunner title="Nightingale Sector Padding" name="nightingale-padding" type="generated" options="{ \"enterprise\": true }" /%}

To create a hole in the middle, `innerRadiusRatio` option should be added to the polar **radius** axis:

```js
axes: [
    {
        type: 'angle-category',
    },
    {
        type: 'radius-number',
        innerRadiusRatio: 0.5
    },
]
```

{% chartExampleRunner title="Nightingale Hole in the Middle" name="nightingale-hole" type="generated" options="{ \"enterprise\": true }" /%}

Please see the API reference for more polar axes style options.

